      • reference2ShortEntrySet

        public ObjectSortedSet<Reference2ShortMap.Entry<K>> reference2ShortEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Reference2ShortMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Reference2ShortMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
